Description: Automatic keyboard layout switching for EN/RU/UA on Linux
 Switchamba is an intelligent keyboard layout auto-switcher that
 detects the language you are typing in and automatically switches
 your keyboard layout between English, Russian, and Ukrainian.
 .
 Features:
  - Real-time keystroke analysis using n-gram statistics
  - Dictionary-based language validation
  - Optional AWS Bedrock (Claude) disambiguation for ambiguous words
  - Double-Ctrl line correction via Claude Sonnet
  - Double-Alt manual word reliteration cycling
  - GNOME Shell panel indicator with color-coded layout display
  - Per-channel correction statistics
